      "span_text": "H · c 2 (X 6 ) =m(M + 8) and D α · c 2 (X 6 ) = 0 otherwise. (9.5) In particular, c 2 (X 6 ) = 0, which means that X 6 is not the quotient of an abelian threefold. (9.6) This result has important implications for worldsheet instantons corrections in the type IIA compactification on X 6 , since it is expected that most (all?) Calabi-Yau manifolds that are not quotients of abelian threefolds contain rational curves  .",
